{A very clear win for White in the dubious Nh5-f5 system} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nf3 g6 7. h3 Bg7 8. Bf4 O-O 9. e3 a6 10. a4 Nh5 11. Bh2 f5 {This approach doesn't work at all.} 12. Be2 f4 13. O-O {This position is completely winning for White.} Bh6 (13... fxe3 14. fxe3 Bh6 15. Qd3 {Black's pieces are misplaced.}) 14. Nd2 {simply not caring about e3, Black's pieces are misplaced and under developed.} fxe3 15. fxe3 Rxf1+ 16. Nxf1 Nf6 17. e4 Qe7 18. e5 dxe5 19. Bc4 Qe8 (19... Qd6 20. Ng3 {planning Ne4 and White is winning automatically.}) 20. Ng3 Nbd7 21. Nge4 Be3+ 22. Kh1 Bd4 23. Qf3 Kg7 24. Rf1 Qf8 25. Qe2 Qe8 26. d6 Rb8 27. Nd5 Nxe4 28. Nc7 Qh8 29. Ne6+ Kh6 30. Qxe4 1-0


