1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nf3 g6 7. Bf4 Bg7 8. h3 O-O 9. e3 Na6 10. Bxa6 bxa6 11. Rc1 { Don't forget to play Rc1. } 11... Rb8 12. b3 a5 13. O-O Nh5 14. Bh2 f5 15. Re1 { planning e4. } 15... Rb4 16. a3 Rb6 17. Nd2 { preparing Nc4 and e4. } 17... Ba6 18. Na4 $16 ( 18. e4 $3 { Once again we can afford to allow ...f4 as the center is in our control. } 18... f4 19. Na4 Rb7 20. e5 Bxe5 21. Nxc5 $16 { The tactics favour White. } ) 18... Rb7 19. Nc4 Bxc4 20. Rxc4 Qe7 21. Qd3 Re8 22. Rb1 Be5 23. Bxe5 Qxe5 24. Qd2 Reb8 25. Qc2 Nf6 26. Nc3 Nxd5 27. Nxd5 Qxd5 28. Rd1 Qe6 29. Rd3 a4 30. Rxa4 Rxb3 31. Rxa7 Rxd3 32. Qxd3 c4 33. Qd4 Rb1+ 34. Kh2 Qe5+ 35. Qxe5 dxe5 36. Rc7 Ra1 37. Rxc4 Rxa3 38. Rc8+ Kg7 39. Rc7+ Kg8 40. Re7 Ra5 41. g4 h5 42. gxf5 gxf5 43. Kg3 f4+ 44. exf4 exf4+ 45. Kxf4 Ra2 46. f3 Rh2 47. Kg3 Rh1 48. h4 Rg1+ 49. Kf4 Rh1 50. Kg5 Rg1+ 51. Kxh5 Kf8 52. Ra7 Rg3 53. f4 Rg1 54. f5 Kg8 55. Kh6 Kf8 56. h5 Kg8 57. f6 Kf8 58. Kh7 Rg2 59. h6 Rf2 60. Kg6 Rg2+ 61. Kf5 Rf2+ 62. Ke5 Re2+ 63. Kd4 Rd2+ 64. Ke3 Rh2 65. h7 1-0[Event "FIDE Grand Swiss"]
