1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 (3. Nc3 {This is also possible but leads to complex theoretical battle.} c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. f4 {with complex theory, something we wish to avoid.}) 3... c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nc3 g6 7. Bf4 a6 8. a4 Bg7 9. h3 O-O 10. e3 Re8 11. Nd2 Nbd7 12. Be2 Ne5 13. O-O Nfd7 14. e4 $1 {After we develop, castle and stabilize our position it makes a lot of sence to start expanding in the center. There are other options like Bh2, Bg3, Qc2 & Re1.} Qe7 15. Re1 g5 16. Bh2 Nf8 17. Bxe5 Bxe5 18. Bg4 (18. Nc4 {Planning Bg4-Ne3-Nf5.} Bxc3 19. bxc3 Qxe4 20. Nxd6 {wins material.}) 18... Ng6 19. Nc4 Qf6 20. Bxc8 Raxc8 21. Qc2 Nh4 22. Ne2 b5 23. axb5 axb5 24. Ne3 Bxb2 25. Ng4 Qg7 26. Rab1 Bd4 27. Nxd4 cxd4 28. Qd3 h5 29. Nh2 Rc3 30. Qxb5 Qe5 31. Qe2 Qh8 32. Rb6 d3 33. Qd2 Qd4 34. Rc6 Rxc6 35. dxc6 Rxe4 36. c7 Rxe1+ 37. Qxe1 d2 38. c8=Q+ Kg7 39. Qd1 Qe4 40. Qc3+ f6 1-0


