{ A very convincing win for White! Demonstrating that a knight is very badly placed on a6 in these lines because it abandons the central squares. } 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5 4. cxb5 a6 5. b6 Qxb6 6. Nc3 d6 7. Nf3 g6 8. Nd2 a5 9. e4 Bg7 10. Bb5+ { Generally speaking: if this check is possible it is good! } 10... Bd7 11. Be2 $16 { White goes back with the bishop, his point being that ...Nbd7 is on longer possible. } ( 11. a4 $16 { is also very good. For example } 11... Bxb5 12. axb5 ( { or } 12. Nxb5 ) 12... O-O 13. Nc4 Qc7 14. O-O Nbd7 15. Bd2 $1 { The bishop is eyeing the weak pawn on a5. } ( 15. h3 Nb6 16. Nxa5 Nbxd5 $13 ) 15... Rfb8 ( 15... Nb6 16. Nxa5 ) 16. b3 $16 ( 16. Qe2 $16 ) ) ( 11. Nc4 $16 Qb7 12. a4 O-O 13. O-O { I give some sample lines: } ( 13. Bxd7 $4 Nfxd7 $1 { Black's idea will soon become clear. } 14. O-O Nb6 $15 15. Na3 ( 15. Ne3 Na6 16. Bd2 c4 $15 ) 15... f5 $1 { Suddenly Black has strong counterplay! } 16. exf5 Rxf5 $17 { [%csl Rd5] } ) 13... Ne8 ( 13... Na6 14. Nxa5 ) ( 13... Bxb5 14. axb5 ) 14. Bg5 { Developing with tempo. } 14... Bxb5 ( 14... f6 { This just ruins Black's position. White is better in many ways: } 15. Bd2 $16 { I like this move best, intending f4 and targeting a5. } ( 15. Bf4 $16 ) ( 15. Bh4 $16 ) ) 15. Nxb5 f6 16. Bd2 $16 ) 11... O-O 12. O-O Na6 13. Nc4 Qc7 14. Bf4 $16 { Why is White just better in all of these lines? Because the usual strategy in the Benko Gambit does not work here. Instead of the a- and b-file he has only the b-file for counterplay - this is not sufficient! } ( 14. Bg5 $16 ) 14... Ne8 15. Qd2 { It is hard to suggest constructive moves for Black. } 15... Bf6 ( { Maybe the desperate } 15... f5 16. exf5 ( 16. e5 $16 ) 16... Bxf5 { but White is just better after for instance } 17. Rae1 $16 { [%csl Re7] } ) 16. Bg3 a4 17. Rab1 Qb8 18. f4 Nac7 19. e5 $18 dxe5 20. fxe5 Bg7 21. Bh4 f6 22. Bf2 fxe5 23. Bxc5 Bf6 24. Nb6 Bf5 25. Rbc1 Ra7 26. g4 Bc8 27. Nxc8 Rb7 28. Nxe7+ Bxe7 29. Bxe7 Rxf1+ 30. Rxf1 Rxb2 31. Qh6 Ng7 32. Rf8+ Qxf8 33. Bxf8 Kxf8 34. Qg5 Nce8 35. Qxe5 a3 36. d6 1-0[Event "Pardubice Skanska op"]
[Site "Pardubice"]
[Date "2004.07.30"]
[Round "8"]
[White "Inarkiev, Ernesto"]
