1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5 4. Nf3 g6 5. cxb5 a6 6. b6 d6 7. Nc3 Nbd7 8. a4 Nxb6 9. a5 ( { or } 9. e4 ) 9... Nbd7 10. e4 Bg7 11. Be2 O-O 12. O-O Ne8 13. Nd2 Nc7 14. Nc4 Nb5 15. Na4 { Our plan is to put a knight on b6 and block Black's play. } 15... Nd4 { Black has a good square in the center. The position is more complicated though still better for White. } 16. Bd3 Ne5 17. Nxe5 Bxe5 18. Nb6 Rb8 19. Bh6 Re8 20. f4 Bh8 21. f5 { White starts attacking - Black's king is short of defenders. } 21... e6 $2 { This is too much of a weakening. } ( { How do we improve the position if Black does "nothing"? For instance } 21... Bb7 22. Bc4 Qc7 23. Ra3 $1 { Including the last piece into play. } 23... Rbd8 24. Rg3 $18 ) ( 21... Rxb6 22. axb6 Qxb6 $16 { could be tried. } ) 22. dxe6 fxe6 23. fxg6 $18 Qh4 ( 23... hxg6 24. Qg4 ) 24. gxh7+ Kxh7 25. Bf4 e5 26. Bg3 Qg5 27. Nxc8 Rbxc8 28. Bxa6 Rc7 29. Bc4 Bf6 30. Rxf6 1-0[Event "Minneapolis HB Global op"]
