1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5 4. Nf3 g6 $6 ( 4... b4 $13 ) 5. cxb5 a6 6. b6 d6 7. Nc3 Nbd7 8. e4 Bg7 9. a4 Qxb6 ( 9... a5 10. Bb5 $1 ) 10. Be2 O-O 11. O-O Rb8 12. Nd2 Ne8 ( 12... a5 13. Nc4 $16 ) 13. a5 Qa7 14. Nc4 $14 Nc7 15. Na4 $3 { This is the plan in this position - occupy b6! } 15... Nb5 16. Nab6 Nxb6 17. Nxb6 $14 ( { Now that it comes with tempo } 17. axb6 $1 { would have also been interesting. } 17... Qb7 18. Re1 Nd4 19. Bf1 $14 ) 17... f5 $2 18. Nxc8 $16 { All of the sudden, white is willing to give up his powerful knight. Because Black played f5, White has the chance to successfully open up the center! } 18... Rbxc8 19. exf5 $1 ( 19. Bf3 $4 f4 20. Rb1 Nd4 $17 { would have been a disaster for white } ) 19... gxf5 20. Bc4 Kh8 21. Re1 Bf6 22. Qh5 Nd4 23. Ra3 Nc2 24. Rh3 e5 25. Rf1 Nd4 26. Bxa6 Rc7 27. Bd3 e4 28. Bh6 Rg8 29. Rg3 Rcc8 30. Bc4 Be5 31. a6 f4 32. Rxg8+ Rxg8 33. Kh1 Qd7 34. g3 Nf3 35. Be2 Nd4 36. gxf4 Bg7 37. Bg4 Qe7 38. Bxg7+ Qxg7 39. h3 Ne2 40. Qf5 e3 41. Qe4 h5 42. Qxe3 hxg4 43. Qxe2 Qh6 44. f3 gxh3 45. Rg1 Rxg1+ 46. Kxg1 Qxf4 47. a7 Qd4+ 48. Kh1 Qa4 49. Qe7 Qd1+ 50. Kh2 Qc2+ 51. Kxh3 Qf5+ 52. Kg3 Qg6+ 53. Kh4 1-0[Event "Pardubice op"]
