{ Another great game with the typical strategy: block the Queenside and attack on the Kingside. } 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5 4. cxb5 a6 5. b6 d6 6. Nc3 Nbd7 7. a4 a5 8. e4 g6 9. Bb5 Bg7 10. Nf3 O-O 11. O-O Nxb6 12. Bf4 ( 12. h3 ) ( 12. Re1 ) 12... Nh5 13. Be3 Bd7 14. Be2 Bg4 15. Qc2 ( 15. Nd2 $2 Bxe2 16. Qxe2 f5 17. exf5 Rxf5 $13 ) ( 15. h3 $1 Bxf3 16. Bxf3 Nf6 17. Be2 Ne8 18. Qc2 Nc7 19. Rad1 Na6 20. Bb5 ( 20. Bxa6 Rxa6 21. b3 $16 ) 20... Nb4 21. Qd2 $18 ) 15... Nf6 16. h3 Bxf3 17. Bxf3 Nc4 18. Bc1 Nd7 19. Be2 Ncb6 20. Be3 Qc7 21. Nb5 Qb7 22. Rab1 Rfc8 23. b3 Rd8 24. Rfd1 Nf6 25. f4 Ne8 26. Bc4 Nc7 27. Nxc7 Qxc7 28. Bb5 $16 e6 $2 { Because Black couldn't stand doing nothing, he decided to do something active. But as it is so often the case, it backfired! } 29. dxe6 $1 fxe6 30. f5 $18 Be5 31. Bg5 Rf8 32. fxe6 Nc8 33. Bd7 Bf6 34. Bxf6 Rxf6 35. Qc3 Rf8 1-0[Event "Brocco op"]

