1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. f4 Rd8 12. O-O b6 13. Ng3 a5 $6 { A very strong player was playing Black, but he nevertheless chose a move there is no room for in this variation! } 14. Qe2 Qa7 $6 { Black tries to carry out the ... Ba6 idea, but the whole setup is visibly unnatural. } 15. e4 ( 15. f5 $1 { This was the best way to punish Black. } 15... e5 16. Bb5 $16 { This is a big problem for Black. The knight, which is the only defender of the e5-point, is under attack, e.g. } 16... Ba6 17. c4 Rac8 18. Bxc6 Rxc6 19. dxe5 $18 ) 15... Ba6 ( 15... cxd4 $2 16. e5 $1 Nd5 17. Qe4 $1 { would be very bad for Black: } 17... g6 18. c4 $1 Nde7 19. Nh5 $18 { and White should break through. } ) 16. e5 Bxd3 17. Qxd3 Ne8 18. f5 cxd4 19. fxe6 Nxe5 ( 19... fxe6 $2 20. Qf3 $18 ) 20. exf7+ Nxf7 21. cxd4 Qd7 22. Nf5 $1 { White plays excellently, keeping up the initiative. } 22... Ned6 23. Nxg7 $1 { With a free-flowing attack. } 23... Kxg7 24. d5 { From a practical standpoint it looks like White is winning. Black's only defence is almost impossible to find. } 24... Rg8 $2 ( 24... Nh8 $3 { still held, but who would find this? } 25. Qc3+ Kg8 26. Bb2 Ng6 27. Rf6 Qg7 28. Raf1 Rac8 29. Rxg6 Rxc3 30. Rxg7+ Kxg7 31. Bxc3+ Kg8 $14 { Black has survived, but White of course still presses for the win. } ) 25. Qg3+ Kf8 26. Bh6+ Ke7 27. Rae1+ 1-0[Event "Chess.com Rapid Wk22 Swiss"]
