1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. f4 b6 12. O-O Rd8 13. Bb2 $6 { We must not allow ...Ng4 (or ...Nd5) with tempo because Black will find the time to play ...f5! } ( 13. Ng3 $1 Bb7 14. Qe2 $14 { Let's see a sample line, continued until the winning conclusion, where White plays the exemplary sacrifice of the pawn on d4: } 14... Ne7 $6 15. e4 $3 cxd4 $6 16. cxd4 Rxd4 17. Bb2 Rdd8 18. Rac1 Qd7 19. Bb5 $18 Bc6 20. Bxc6 Nxc6 21. Bxf6 gxf6 22. Qg4+ Kh8 23. Qh4 $18 Qd4+ 24. Kh1 Rac8 25. Nh5 $18 ) 13... Ne7 $2 { Black doesn't take his chance and allows the e3-e4 push. } ( 13... Ng4 $1 14. Rf3 c4 ( 14... f5 15. c4 ) 15. Bc2 f5 $13 ) 14. e4 $16 { we can clearly see that even super-strong GMs , do not know how to play these positions with black !!! } 14... Ng6 ( 14... Bb7 15. Ng3 Rac8 16. Qe2 $16 ( 16. h3 $5 Ng6 ( 16... Nc6 17. e5 $3 ( 17. Rc1 $16 ) 17... Nd5 18. Qe2 cxd4 19. cxd4 Nce7 ( 19... Qe7 20. Ne4 $16 ) 20. f5 $16 ) 17. Qf3 $16 ) 16... Ng6 17. Qf3 Nh4 18. Qf2 Ng4 19. Qe2 Nf6 20. h3 Ng6 21. Qf2 $16 ) 15. Qd2 $16 { White achieved a big advantage and later won convincingly. } 15... a5 16. Ng3 Ba6 17. f5 Bxd3 18. Qxd3 Ne5 19. Qe2 cxd4 20. cxd4 Nc4 21. Rac1 b5 22. fxe6 fxe6 23. a4 Qb7 ( 23... Qb6 24. Ba1 Rxd4 25. Bxd4 Qxd4+ 26. Kh1 $18 ) 24. Ba1 Rac8 25. Kh1 Na3 26. Rxc8 Qxc8 27. d5 $18 { A typical breakthrough, using the concentrated energy of the white pieces. } 27... Rf8 28. axb5 exd5 29. exd5 Nxd5 30. Rxf8+ Qxf8 31. h3 Qe7 32. Qa2 Qc5 33. b6 Nc4 34. b7 Qb5 35. Qxc4 Qxc4 36. b8 Kf7 37. a7 Ne7 38. axa5 Qe6 39. e5 Qxe5 40. Bxe5 h6 41. Ba1 Nc6 42. Kg1 g6 43. Ne4 Ke6 44. Nf2 Ne7 45. Ng4 h5 46. Ne3 Nc6 47. Kf2 Nb4 48. Kf3 Nd3 49. Ke4 Nf2+ 50. Kf4 Nd3+ 51. Kg5 Kf7 52. Nc4 Ne1 53. Ne5+ Ke6 54. Nxg6 Nxg2 55. Nf4+ Nxf4 56. Kxf4 1-0[Event "Chess.com Rapid Wk18 Swiss"]
