1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. f4 Rd8 12. O-O b6 13. Bb2 $6 ( { White should start with } 13. Ng3 ) 13... Bb7 $6 ( 13... Ng4 $1 { punishes 13.Bb2?! } 14. Rf3 c4 ( 14... f5 ) 15. Bc2 f5 $13 ) 14. Ng3 Rd7 15. Rc1 Rad8 16. Qe2 Qb8 { Black has put pressure on d4 to stop e3-e4, but he runs out of other useful ideas. } ( 16... Ne7 { If Black removes the pressure from d4, we can immediately proceed with } 17. e4 $1 ) 17. h3 Ne7 { In the end Black allows e3-e4. He probably shouldn't have done that, but White would have gradually improved his position while Black was struggling to find useful moves. } 18. e4 $16 Ng6 19. Qe3 Qa8 20. Rce1 a5 21. Rf2 Re8 ( { If } 21... Ba6 { White simply preserves the bishop: } 22. Bc2 { This was the idea of 21.Rf2 } ) 22. a4 Bc6 23. Bc2 Qb7 24. Ba1 cxd4 25. cxd4 b5 { Black tries to lash out, but it only worsens his predicament. } 26. d5 $1 { After this decisive breakthrough White easily gains the winning position, but later he loses, owing to the short time control. } 26... exd5 27. Bxf6 gxf6 28. Nh5 d4 29. Nxf6+ Kh8 30. Qg3 Rde7 31. f5 Qb8 32. Qxb8 Rxb8 33. fxg6 hxg6 34. axb5 Rxb5 35. Ba4 Rc5 36. Bxc6 Rxc6 37. Nd5 Ra7 38. Rd1 Rc4 39. Rfd2 d3 40. Rxd3 Rxe4 41. Ra1 Re5 42. Nc3 Rc7 43. Ra2 Kg7 44. Na4 Rc1+ 45. Kh2 f5 46. Rc3 Rf1 47. Rf3 Rc1 48. Kg3 g5 49. Rb2 Kg6 50. Rfb3 Kh5 51. Rb5 f4+ 52. Kf2 Ree1 53. Rxa5 Kh4 54. Nc5 Rf1+ 55. Ke2 Rfe1+ 56. Kf3 Rf1+ 57. Ke4 Rce1+ 58. Kf5 f3 59. gxf3 Rxf3+ 60. Kg6 Rxh3 61. Nd3 Rxd3 62. Rbb5 Rd6+ 63. Kf5 Rf1+ 64. Ke5 Rdf6 65. Rb8 R6f5+ 0-1[Event "Chess.com Rapid Wk24 Swiss"]
