1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. f4 b6 12. O-O Rd8 13. Bb2 $6 { Grischuk committed the same inaccuracy in a number of games. } ( { We already know that we should start with } 13. Ng3 $1 ) 13... Bb7 $6 ( { And Black should play } 13... Ng4 $1 ) 14. Ng3 Na5 15. Qe2 Rac8 16. Rad1 $14 ( { The thematic advance also needs to be considered: } 16. e4 Nb3 $1 ( 16... cxd4 17. cxd4 Nc4 18. Rac1 b5 19. Ba1 $16 { Black is in a tough spot. } ) 17. e5 $1 c4 $1 18. Bb1 $1 Nd7 19. Ra2 b5 20. f5 { The engine points out that Black is able to survive after } 20... Nxe5 $13 { with tremendous complications. } ) 16... cxd4 17. cxd4 Nc4 18. Rc1 b5 19. a4 a6 20. axb5 axb5 21. e4 Qb6 22. Ba1 Ra8 23. Kh1 Ra3 24. f5 exf5 25. Nxf5 Rxd3 26. Qxd3 Bxe4 27. Qg3 Bxf5 28. Rxf5 Nd5 29. h3 Qd6 30. Qxd6 Rxd6 31. Re1 f6 32. Re8+ Kf7 33. Rb8 Nce3 34. Rf3 Rc6 35. Bb2 b4 36. Rb7+ Kg8 37. Rf2 h5 38. Re2 Kh7 39. Kg1 Nd1 40. Rd2 N1e3 41. Re2 Nd1 42. Rb5 N1c3 43. Bxc3 bxc3 44. Rc5 Rd6 45. Kf2 g5 46. Kf3 Kg6 47. g3 f5 48. Re5 g4+ 49. hxg4 hxg4+ 50. Ke2 Nf6 51. Rxc3 Ne4 52. Rxe4 fxe4 53. Ke3 Re6 54. Rc5 Rf6 55. Kxe4 Rf3 56. d5 Kf6 57. d6 Ke6 58. Rd5 Kd7 59. Rd3 Rf1 60. Ke5 Rf2 61. Rd4 Re2+ 62. Kf5 Rf2+ 63. Kxg4 Rf1 64. Kg5 Rf3 65. g4 Rf1 66. Kg6 Rf2 67. g5 Rf1 68. Kg7 Rf2 69. g6 Rf1 70. Kg8 Rf2 71. g7 Rf1 72. Rh4 1-0[Event "Julius Baer GenCup Prelim"]
