{This rapid game by two super strong GMs shows once again that Black's position may collapse at any moment after an inaccurate move!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. f4 b6 12. O-O Rd8 13. Ng3 Bb7 14. Bb2 $14 (14. Qe2 $14 Rac8 15. Bb2 Na5 16. Rad1 cxd4 17. cxd4 Nc4 18. Rc1 b5 19. f5 $16) 14... c4 $2 {Now White's center is left unchallenged!} 15. Bc2 $16 e5 $4 16. fxe5 Nxe5 17. e4 $18 (17. Rxf6 $3 gxf6 18. Qh5 (18. Nh5) 18... Ng6 19. e4 Rd6 20. Rf1 $18 Re6 21. Bc1) 17... Qc6 18. Qd2 Nd3 19. Bxd3 cxd3 20. Rae1 $18 Re8 21. e5 Nd7 22. Nf5 f6 23. Re3 g6 24. Nd6 fxe5 25. Nxe8 Rxe8 26. c4 Qxc4 27. dxe5 Nc5 28. e6 Ne4 29. Qb4 Qxb4 30. axb4 d2 31. Rd1 Bd5 32. e7 Rxe7 33. Rxd2 Bb7 34. Rd8+ Kf7 35. b5 a6 36. bxa6 Bxa6 37. Rh8 Ng5 38. Rxe7+ Kxe7 39. h4 Nf7 40. Rxh7 Bd3 41. h5 gxh5 42. Rxh5 b5 43. Rc5 Kd6 44. Ba3 Ke6 45. Kf2 Ne5 46. Bb2 Nd7 47. Rg5 b4 48. Ke3 Bc2 49. Rb5 b3 50. g4 Nf8 51. Kf4 Kf7 52. Kg5 Ne6+ 53. Kh6 Nf4 54. g5 Ke7 55. Rb6 Kd7 56. Be5 Nd3 57. Bd4 Nf4 58. Rf6 Nd5 59. Rf7+ Ke6 60. Rb7 Nf4 61. Rb5 Kd7 62. Bc3 Ke6 63. Kg7 Nh5+ 64. Kf8 Nf4 65. Re5+ Kd7 66. Kf7 Kc6 67. Re1 Kc5 68. Bf6 Kc4 69. Ra1 Ng6 70. Ra6 Kb5 71. Ra8 Nh4 72. Rc8 Ng6 73. Bb2 Nf4 74. Kf6 Nd5+ 75. Ke5 Ne7 76. Ke6 Ng6 77. Kd6 Kb4 78. Rc5 Ka4 79. Bc3 b2 80. Bxb2 Kb3 81. Bd4 Be4 82. Ke6 Kb4 83. Kf6 Nh4 84. Bf2 Ng6 85. Rc8 1-0

