{A very good game by White... please be aware of the improvement on move 14 - 14.Qe2! because in these positions we do not want to allow the move ...Nd5 (or ...Ng4) with tempo, and then black has the time to play ...f7-f5! complicating matters !} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. f4 b6 12. O-O Bb7 13. Ng3 Rad8 (13... Na5 $5 14. Rb1 $1 (14. Bb2 $2 Nd5 15. Qe2 c4 16. Bc2 f5 $13) 14... Rfd8 15. Qe2 Rac8 16. Bb2 $14) 14. Bb2 (14. Qe2 $16 Nd5 15. c4 $16 Nf6 16. dxc5 bxc5 17. Bb2 $16) 14... Qd7 $6 (14... Nd5 $3 15. Qd2 cxd4 16. cxd4 f5 $13) 15. Qe2 $16 cxd4 16. cxd4 Nd5 17. f5 $18 (17. Rad1 $2 f5 $13) 17... exf5 18. Bxf5 Qe7 19. e4 Nc7 20. Bxh7+ Kxh7 21. Qh5+ Kg8 22. Nf5 Qxe4 23. Rae1 Qd5 24. Qg5 g6 25. Qf6 gxf5 26. Qg5+ Kh7 27. Re3 1-0

