1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. f4 b6 12. O-O Ne7 { This is probably the best idea for Black, trying to fight on the light squares! } 13. Ng3 Nf5 14. Qe2 cxd4 15. cxd4 Bb7 ( { In the theory section we saw } 15... Qd7 $1 ) ( { and } 15... Nxg3 ) 16. Nxf5 exf5 17. Bxf5 Rfe8 18. Bd2 ( 18. Bd3 $1 { was more accurate, when it's not so easy for Black to get fully sufficient counterplay: } 18... Be4 19. Bd2 Bxd3 20. Qxd3 Ne4 21. Rac1 Qd7 ( 21... Qe7 22. Bb4 ) 22. Rfd1 $14 ) 18... Rad8 19. Qd3 Bd5 20. Rfc1 Qb7 21. Bh3 h5 22. a4 a6 23. Qe2 Be6 $2 { An unfortunate exchange. Without it, Black's compensation was already more than satisfactory. } 24. Bxe6 Rxe6 25. Qf3 Qd5 $6 { One more inaccuracy and White starts pressing for the win. } ( 25... Qe4 $44 { was a better square. The knight should occupy e4 after the exchange, not d5! } ) 26. a5 b5 27. f5 Re7 28. Qxd5 Nxd5 29. Kf2 Rd6 30. Rc8+ Kh7 31. Kf3 g5 32. h3 Rf6 33. g4 hxg4+ 34. hxg4 Rh6 35. Re1 Rh2 36. Re2 Rh3+ 37. Kg2 Rh4 38. e4 b4 39. Kg3 Nf6 40. e5 b3 41. Rb8 Rxg4+ 42. Kf3 Rh4 43. Bxg5 Rh5 44. Rh8+ 1-0[Event "World Blitz 2022"]

