{White was pressing in this blitz game, but he played the d4-d5 advance prematurely.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Bd3 b6 11. e4 Ba6 12. O-O Bxd3 13. Qxd3 Nc6 14. Bg5 Nd7 15. Rad1 Na5 16. Bf4 e5 17. Bg3 Rfe8 18. d5 $6 {Black will get a good blockade.} ({A cool-headed move like} 18. h3 $14 {, would have preserved a small, but definite edge.}) 18... c4 19. Qf3 Qd6 $2 (19... Nb7 $1 {was good for Black, because} 20. Nd4 {can be met with} Nd6 $11) 20. Bh4 $2 (20. Nd4 $16 {Both sides failed to notice this tactical idea! Quite typical for the blitz time control.}) 20... f6 21. Qg4 Kh8 22. Bg3 Nb3 23. h4 Ndc5 24. h5 Nd3 25. Bh4 Nf4 26. Nxf4 exf4 27. f3 Rad8 28. h6 g5 29. Bf2 Qxa3 30. Bd4 Nxd4 31. Rxd4 Qxc3 32. Rfd1 Qe3+ 33. Kh2 c3 34. Rc4 Qe2 35. Rdd4 Qe1 36. Rc7 b5 37. Qh5 Qg3+ 38. Kh1 Qe1+ 39. Kh2 Qg3+ 40. Kh1 Qe1+ 41. Kh2 1/2-1/2

