1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 { And now we will study some minor tries by Black (and yet quite common in amateur's games) . All of them fail to equalize and white gets a nice advantage by following the simple plan of Ne2-0-0 and then expanding in the center with e3-e4 (sometimes we may go e3-e4 even before castling!!) . } 4... Bxc3+ $6 { PREMATURE... Let us now study the typical plans } ( 4... d6 $6 { A bit passive } 5. Bd3 O-O 6. Ne2 $1 c5 7. O-O Nc6 8. Bc2 $14 { We gain the bishop pair with a3, e.g. } ( 8. a3 { This is a good alternative. } 8... Bxc3 9. Nxc3 $14 cxd4 10. exd4 Nxd4 11. Bxh7+ Nxh7 12. Qxd4 $16 ) 8... Qe7 9. a3 Bxc3 10. Nxc3 ) ( 4... O-O 5. Bd3 b6 ( 5... d6 $6 { Against non-combative play like this, we achieve Nge2 and a3 with a nice centre and a bishop pair! } 6. Ne2 b6 7. O-O Bb7 8. a3 Bxc3 9. Nxc3 $16 { The game is already one-sided, e.g. } 9... Nbd7 10. e4 e5 11. d5 Re8 12. f3 Nf8 13. Be3 Ng6 14. g3 $16 { White can gradually prepare an attack on both flanks! } ) 6. Ne2 $1 Bb7 7. a3 $3 Be7 ( 7... Bxc3+ 8. Nxc3 Bxg2 $2 9. Rg1 Bb7 10. e4 $18 { White has a winning attack with his open g-file and the support of the 2 bishops! } ) 8. e4 $16 { We should not lose the chance to expand in the center!!Black cannot even fight back: } ( 8. O-O $6 d5 $14 ) 8... d5 $2 9. cxd5 exd5 10. e5 Ne4 11. Qc2 f5 12. Nf4 $18 { Black's position crumbles. } ) ( 4... O-O 5. Bd3 Bxc3+ $6 6. bxc3 { transposes to 4...Bxc3+?! } ) 5. bxc3 O-O 6. Bd3 d6 7. Ne2 $1 ( 7. Nf3 $2 { That's a big mistake!! WHEN WE HAVE DOUBLED C-PAWNS, THE KNIGHT BELONGS TO e2!!! REMEMBER THIS SIMPLE RULE!! } 7... e5 $13 ) 7... Re8 8. e4 e5 9. f3 $16 Nbd7 10. Be3 $16 ( { White can also start expanding on the Kingside: } 10. h4 $16 c5 11. d5 Nf8 12. g4 N6d7 13. Ng3 f6 14. a4 b6 15. Ra2 Ba6 16. Rg2 Rb8 17. O-O $16 ) 10... c5 11. d5 Nf8 12. Qd2 $16 Ng6 13. O-O $16 { It doesn't matter if we castle or not... Black cannot carry out his only pawn brake ...f5 and of course, he can't put pressure on our c4 pawn... White has a free hand on the Kingside and he is much better! } ( 13. h4 $16 ) *[Event "MODERN CHESS"]
