1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 c5 6. Ne2 d5 7. cxd5 cxd4 8. exd4 Nxd5 9. O-O Nc6 10. Nxd5 Qxd5 11. a3 Be7 12. Be3 Bf6 13. Qc2 g6 14. Rfd1 Qd8 15. Be4 Bd7 ( { Black is not able to block the d5-square without problems with } 15... Ne7 { , White immediately fights for control of the d5-square: } 16. Nc3 Nd5 17. Bxd5 exd5 18. Qb3 $1 { Black is forced to give up a pawn without full compensation. } 18... Be6 19. Qxb7 Rb8 20. Qxa7 Rxb2 21. Na4 $14 ) 16. d5 { After this break White gets a risk-free advantage, even though there are serious chances for Black to draw. } 16... exd5 17. Bxd5 Qc8 18. Rac1 Ne7 19. Qb1 Bc6 20. Bxc6 Nxc6 21. Nf4 { The knight threatens to jump to d5. } 21... Be5 22. b4 Bxf4 23. Bxf4 Qg4 24. Be3 $16 { With the pawn back on g7, Black would be fine, but now with the constant weakness of the Kingside, she is in trouble. White managed to win the game, although many mistakes were committed in the meantime. } 24... Rfd8 25. h3 Qh4 26. b5 Nd4 27. Rc7 Nf5 28. Rxd8+ Qxd8 29. Bf4 Qd5 30. Kh2 Re8 31. Qc2 Nh4 32. f3 Nxf3+ 33. Kg3 Nd4 34. Qc4 Ne2+ 35. Kh2 Qf5 36. Bd6 Qf6 37. Qc5 b6 38. Rc8 Qe6 39. Rxe8+ Qxe8 40. Qe5 Qd7 41. Be7 f6 42. Qxe2 Qc7+ 43. g3 Kf7 44. Bb4 h5 45. Kg2 Qd7 46. Qe4 Qd8 47. Qc4+ Kg7 48. Qe6 Qd4 49. h4 Qb2+ 50. Kf3 g5 51. Qe7+ Kg6 52. Qe8+ Kh7 53. Qf7+ Kh8 54. hxg5 fxg5 55. Qxh5+ Kg7 56. Qxg5+ Kf7 57. Qf5+ Kg7 58. Qd3 1-0[Event "EU-ch blitz (Women)"]
