1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. Ne2 ( { Our move is } 6. a3 { The game transposed to our repertoire anyway. } ) 6... c5 7. cxd5 cxd4 8. exd4 Nxd5 9. O-O Nc6 10. Nxd5 Qxd5 11. Be3 h6 12. Nf4 Qd8 13. Nh5 $1 { A strong aggressive move. Ideas of Qg4 begin to appear. } 13... e5 ( 13... f5 { is a lesser evil, but White will easily readjust his pieces to target the e6-pawn: } 14. Bc4 $16 ) ( 13... Ne7 $2 14. Qg4 $18 ) 14. d5 Nd4 $2 ( 14... Ne7 $1 { was obligatory: } 15. Qf3 $1 Ng6 $14 { and Black is able to hold, but is still worse. } ) 15. f4 $1 { White is already winning! } 15... Qh4 ( 15... Qxd5 16. f5 $18 ) 16. Bf2 ( 16. fxe5 $1 { was simpler: } 16... Bg4 17. Rf4 Bxd1 18. Rxh4 Bxh5 19. Bxd4 $18 ) 16... Qg4 17. fxe5 Bc5 18. Qxg4 Bxg4 19. Nf4 Rfe8 20. h3 Bd7 21. Rae1 Bb6 22. Kh1 Rad8 23. Bc4 Bb5 24. Bxb5 Nxb5 25. Bxb6 axb6 26. e6 fxe6 27. dxe6 Rd2 28. e7 Rd7 29. Ng6 Kh7 30. Nf8+ 1-0[Event "EU-ch rapid"]
