1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 c5 6. Ne2 d5 7. cxd5 cxd4 8. exd4 Nxd5 9. O-O Nc6 10. Nxd5 exd5 11. Nf4 Bd6 ( 11... Nxd4 12. Bxh7+ Kxh7 13. Qxd4 $16 ) 12. Re1 ( 12. Be3 { is clearly less accurate: } 12... Bxf4 13. Bxf4 Qf6 14. Be3 Bf5 15. Bxf5 Qxf5 { If the major pieces are exchanged, we reach the famous endgame Saidy-Fischer, included in the file. It is beneficial to know the ideas of this endgame and make sure to try to achieve the knight side of it and avoid the bishop side. } ) 12... Qf6 ( 12... Bxf4 13. Bxf4 Qf6 { This no longer works so well because of } 14. Be5 $1 Nxe5 15. Rxe5 ( 15. dxe5 $14 ) 15... Be6 16. Qd2 Rac8 17. Rae1 $14 { with a risk-free pressure for White. White has the more active pieces and the better bishop. } ) 13. Nxd5 Qxd4 14. Be3 Qh4 15. g3 Qg4 16. Bf1 Qxd1 17. Raxd1 { The position is not equal at all. White has much more active pieces and intends to press. } 17... Rd8 ( 17... Bg4 $6 18. Nf6+ gxf6 19. Rxd6 $14 ) 18. Bg5 Bg4 ( 18... f6 { runs into } 19. Bc4 $1 fxg5 ( 19... Kh8 20. Nxf6 $18 ) 20. Nc7+ $18 ) 19. Bxd8 Bxd1 20. Bc7 Bf3 21. Nb6 axb6 22. Bxd6 { Black is close to fully equalizing, but after some inaccurate moves White's advantage grows and White wins without problems. This shows that serious accuracy is required from Black if he wants to hold these positions. } 22... Nd4 23. Be5 Nc6 24. Bc3 $16 { The bishop is now ideally placed on c3. } 24... Bd5 25. a3 f6 26. f4 Kf7 27. Rd1 $16 Bb3 $4 { A blunder in a tough position. } 28. Rd7+ Kg6 29. Bd3+ Kh6 30. f5 Re8 31. Bd2+ Kh5 32. Rxg7 Bd5 33. Kf2 Re7 34. Rxe7 1-0[Event "Platja d'Aro Legends blitz"]
