1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 g6 5. Nc3 Bg7 { move order doesn't matter. } 6. h3 O-O 7. Qb3 a6 { This is a completely new move with no theory. } 8. a4 a5 { Black is planning e6 and recapture on d5 with e-pawn. } ( 8... e6 9. a5 { of course. } ) 9. Bd2 { missing the chance. } ( 9. cxd5 $1 { important decision missed by Ernst. } 9... Nxd5 10. Nxd5 cxd5 11. Bd2 Nc6 12. Bb5 { White will use the c-file and the b5-square to penetrate. Black's g7 bishop is misplaced and out of action. } 12... Bd7 13. O-O e6 14. Rfc1 Rc8 15. Rc3 { Doubling the rooks. White has very good chances. } ) 9... e6 10. Be2 Na6 11. O-O Re8 12. Rfd1 Nb4 13. Rac1 Qe7 14. Be1 h6 15. Bf1 Nd7 16. Na2 Nxa2 17. Qxa2 { no side has a real plan. } 17... dxc4 18. Bxc4 e5 19. d5 cxd5 20. Bxd5 Nb6 21. e4 g5 22. Bb3 Rf8 23. Rd3 Kh8 24. Rdc3 f5 25. Rc7 Qd6 26. Qb1 Nd7 27. exf5 Nf6 28. Qc2 e4 29. Rd1 Qb6 30. Ne5 Bxf5 31. Nf7+ Rxf7 32. Bxf7 e3 33. Qc5 Qxc5 34. Rxc5 e2 35. Rdc1 Bh7 36. Rc8+ 1-0[Event "Bundesliga 1314"]
