1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. e3 O-O 6. Qb3 c6 7. h3 b6 8. Be2 Bb7 9. O-O ( 9. cxd5 { White didn't take on d5 because this can open up the c6-square for Black's knight. } 9... cxd5 10. Bd2 Nc6 { Just what I mentioned. } ) 9... Nbd7 ( 9... dxc4 10. Qxc4 { We are not afraid of Bc6, remmember the exchange of light squared bishops favours White. } 10... Ba6 11. Qa4 Bxe2 12. Nxe2 { e4 comming up. } ) 10. cxd5 { Capturing now makes much more sense. } 10... cxd5 11. Bd2 Qb8 12. Rfc1 { planning a4-a5 and taking control of the c-file. } 12... e5 13. dxe5 Nxe5 14. Be1 Nxf3+ 15. Bxf3 Qe5 16. Rc2 Rfd8 17. Rd1 Rd7 18. Rcd2 Rad8 19. Qb5 Bf8 20. Ne2 Ne4 21. Bxe4 Qxe4 22. Rd4 Qe6 23. Bc3 Bc5 24. R4d2 d4 25. Bxd4 Bd6 26. Qg5 Be7 27. Qh6 Bf8 28. Qf4 Bd6 29. Qg4 f5 30. Qg5 Be7 31. Qg3 Bd6 32. Nf4 Qxa2 33. Be5 Bxe5 34. Rxd7 Rxd7 35. Rxd7 Qb1+ 36. Kh2 Qe4 37. Qg5 Bg7 38. Qd8+ Bf8 39. Qf6 1-0[Event "Paris-ch"]
