1. Nf3 d5 2. d4 Nf6 3. c4 c6 4. e3 g6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Qb3 O-O { The move order doesn't matter, we are here for ideas. } 7. a4 Ne4 ( 7... b6 { makes White's task ever easier. } 8. a5 bxa5 9. Qa3 { pressurizing the a5 pawn. } ) 8. cxd5 Nxc3 9. bxc3 cxd5 10. Ba3 Nc6 11. Bb5 Bg4 12. Nd2 a6 13. Bd3 Na5 14. Qb2 Qd7 15. Qb6 Nc6 16. Nb3 Rab8 17. Nc5 Qd8 18. Rb1 Na5 19. Qxd8 Rfxd8 20. Nb3 Nxb3 21. Rxb3 { White has awesome endgame prospects. } 21... Re8 22. Kd2 Bd7 23. Rhb1 Bxa4 24. Rxb7 Bb5 25. Rxb8 Rxb8 26. Bxe7 Bf8 27. Bxf8 Kxf8 28. e4 dxe4 29. Bxe4 Rd8 30. Bd3 Bc6 31. g3 a5 32. Rb6 Bg2 33. Ra6 Rd5 34. Ke3 h5 35. c4 Rd7 36. Rxa5 Rb7 37. Rb5 Ra7 38. d5 Ke7 39. Rb2 Ra1 40. Rb7+ Kf6 41. Rb6+ Ke7 42. d6+ Kd7 43. c5 Ra3 44. Kd4 Ra4+ 45. Ke5 Bc6 46. Bb5 Re4+ 47. Kf6 Bxb5 48. Rxb5 Re2 49. Rb7+ Kc8 50. Rxf7 Rxf2+ 51. Kxg6 1-0[Event "Elgoibar 16th"]
