1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Nf3 O-O 5. Bg5 d6 6. e3 h6 7. Bh4 Nbd7 8. Be2 Re8 9. O-O c6 10. Qc2 e5 11. Rfd1 $16 ( 11. dxe5 $5 dxe5 12. Nd2 $14 ) ( { Absolutely not } 11. a4 $2 a5 $1 ) ( 11. h3 $5 Qe7 12. Bg3 $16 ) 11... Qc7 ( 11... exd4 { In general we take back with the knight on d4. } 12. Rxd4 $1 { is strong in this concrete position. } ( 12. Nxd4 $1 ) ( 12. exd4 { is also possible. } ) ) ( 11... Qe7 12. h3 $5 ) ( 11... e4 { as usual does not work so well. } 12. Nd2 $16 { White's attack on the Queenside will be very strong, e.g. } ( 12. Nxe4 Rxe4 13. Qxe4 g5 14. Qc2 gxh4 15. Nxh4 $14 { is probably good for White but there is no need to go for such an adventure. } ) 12... g5 13. Bg3 d5 14. cxd5 cxd5 15. Nb5 $18 ) 12. b4 ( 12. h3 $5 Nh5 $2 { with the idea of ...g5 is too slow: } ( 12... g5 13. Bg3 { The bishop is placed annoyingly opposite Black's queen. } ) 13. dxe5 dxe5 14. Nd2 $16 ( 14. Ne4 $16 ) 14... Nhf6 15. Nde4 Nxe4 16. Nxe4 Bf8 17. c5 ( 17. Rxd7 Bxd7 18. Nf6+ Kg7 19. Nxe8+ Rxe8 ) ) 12... g5 13. Bg3 Nh5 { Otherwise White would play h3 next and keep his bishop. } 14. Rab1 ( 14. Nxg5 $2 { does not work here as the Black king has an escape square. } 14... Nxg3 15. Qh7+ Kf8 16. fxg3 Nf6 $1 17. Qc2 hxg5 $19 ) 14... Nxg3 15. hxg3 $16 Nf8 ( 15... exd4 16. Nxd4 Nf6 17. b5 c5 18. b6 $1 ( 18. Nf5 Bxf5 19. Qxf5 $16 { is also strategically lost for Black. } ) 18... axb6 19. Ndb5 $18 ) 16. dxe5 $3 dxe5 { White has many interesting options. } 17. Ne4 ( 17. Bd3 ) ( 17. e4 $2 Ne6 { [%csl Rd4] } ) ( 17. Bd3 ) ( 17. c5 { Vacating c4 for the white knight. } 17... f5 18. Nd2 g4 19. Nc4 ) 17... Be6 ( { Let's see what can happen after } 17... Bf5 { or } 18. Nf6+ ( 18. Bd3 $16 ) 18... Bxf6 19. Qxf5 Bg7 { Now Black is threatening to play ...e4. } 20. Nd2 $1 { Preventing e4 and improving the knight. } ( 20. e4 ) ( 20. Bd3 ) 20... Qc8 21. Bg4 { Aiming for a strategically winning endgame. Possibly keeping the queens on the board with 21.Qc2+- is even stronger. } 21... Qxf5 22. Bxf5 Rad8 23. Ne4 Nh7 24. Bxh7+ { Making sure that the knights won't be exchanged. White's knight is much stronger than Black's bishop. Maybe there are more direct continuations but I want to show the strategic theme. } ( 24. g4 Nf6 ) 24... Kxh7 25. g4 $1 { Fixing the structure is here far more important than for example centralising the king. } ( 25. Kf1 f5 26. Nd2 e4 { [%csl Gg7] } ) 25... Kg6 26. f3 f5 27. gxf5+ Kxf5 28. g4+ Kg6 29. Kf2 $16 ) 18. Nd6 Red8 19. Nf5 $14 ( 19. c5 $16 { is even stronger. } ) 19... Ng6 20. g4 ( 20. Bd3 Bxf5 21. Bxf5 Ne7 22. g4 Nxf5 23. Qxf5 Bf8 24. Nh2 Bg7 25. Nf1 $16 { [%cal Yf1g3] } ) 20... Bf8 21. Rxd8 Rxd8 22. Nd2 Qc8 23. c5 ( 23. Ne4 $1 Bxf5 24. gxf5 Qxf5 25. Bg4 $1 Rd2 $5 26. Bxf5 Rxc2 27. Nf6+ Kg7 28. Nh5+ Kg8 29. Bxc2 $18 ) 23... h5 24. Ne4 Bxf5 ( 24... hxg4 25. Nf6+ ( 25. Bxg4 Bxf5 26. Nf6+ Kg7 27. Bxf5 Qc7 28. Nh5+ Kh6 29. Ng3 $18 ) 25... Kh8 26. Bxg4 $18 ) 25. Nf6+ Kh8 ( 25... Kg7 26. Nxh5+ Kh6 27. gxf5 $18 ) 26. gxf5 $18 Ne7 27. e4 a5 28. Qb3 Nd5 29. exd5 Qxf5 30. Nxh5 cxd5 31. a3 g4 32. Ng3 Qe6 33. Qc2 e4 34. bxa5 e3 35. Rb6 exf2+ 36. Kxf2 Qe5 37. Rb4 Bh6 38. Qd3 d4 39. Nf5 Bf4 ( 39... g3+ 40. Ke1 $18 ( 40. Nxg3 $2 Be3+ 41. Kf3 $4 Qf4# ) ) 40. g3 Rd5 41. Bxg4 Bg5 42. Rxd4 Rxc5 43. Qe4 Qf6 44. Rc4 Qb2+ 45. Be2 Re5 46. Qh1+ 1-0[Event "North American op 19th"]
