1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Nf3 O-O 5. Bg5 d6 6. e3 Nbd7 7. Be2 { Even for the experienced Grandmaster with the white pieces it can sometimes make sense to play lines that are based on a general understanding. } 7... c6 8. Qc2 { With this move White sets a trap. } ( 8. O-O { is possible. } ) 8... Qc7 { This is a very bad position for Black and a dream position for White! Without any concrete theory and with very simple plans White achieves a nice advantage! The Smyslov King's Indian at its best! } ( { If } 8... h6 9. Bh4 g5 ( { If he now plays } 9... Qc7 { then } 10. h3 { [%cal Yh4g3] is an interesting move. } 10... e5 ( 10... Nh5 $2 { can be answered by } 11. g4 ) 11. Bg3 ) 10. Bg3 Nh5 $2 { then White has } 11. Nxg5 $1 ) 9. O-O e5 10. Rfd1 ( 10. b4 h6 11. Bh4 exd4 12. Nxd4 Ne5 13. h3 a6 14. Rad1 ( 14. f4 Ned7 ) 14... c5 15. bxc5 dxc5 16. Nf3 ) 10... Re8 11. Rac1 $5 ( 11. b4 $14 ) ( 11. dxe5 $5 dxe5 ( { or } 11... Nxe5 12. Nd4 ) 12. Nd2 { [%cal Yd2e4] If Black is allowed two moves in a row he could prevent White's plan with ...a5 and ...Nc5 - but this is not possible... } 12... Nc5 ( 12... a5 13. Nde4 h6 14. Bh4 g5 15. Bg3 Nxe4 16. Nxe4 $16 ) 13. b4 Ne6 14. Bxf6 $5 ( 14. Bh4 ) 14... Bxf6 15. Nde4 Be7 16. c5 $16 ) ( { Maybe also } 11. Bh4 { and after } 11... h6 12. h3 ) 11... Nf8 12. b4 Ne6 ( { After } 12... Bf5 { simply } 13. Qb3 { and if } 13... e4 14. Nd2 $16 { [%cal Yc4c5,Yb4b5] } ) 13. Bxf6 $5 { White gives up his bishop to transfer his knight to d6 with gain of tempo. } 13... Bxf6 14. Ne4 Be7 15. dxe5 dxe5 16. c5 $16 { [%csl Gd6,Ge4][%cal Ye4d6] } 16... f6 17. Bc4 Kg7 18. Bb3 { Probably with the idea of Nf3-d2-c4 or in some cases Qc4. } 18... Nd8 19. Nd6 Bxd6 { Now both captures give White a serious advantage. } 20. cxd6 $18 { Now White's idea should be to open the position (e.g. with b4-b5) and activate his pieces. Or to provoke some weaknesses as he did in the game. } ( 20. Rxd6 $16 ) 20... Qd7 21. a4 ( 21. b5 $18 ) 21... b6 22. h3 Bb7 23. a5 $1 { [%cal Yf3d2,Yd2c4] } 23... Nf7 24. Nd2 Red8 25. Nc4 $18 c5 26. bxc5 bxc5 27. f3 Rac8 28. Rd2 Bc6 29. Rcd1 Bb5 30. Qa2 Rc6 31. Ba4 a6 32. Qb3 Rb8 33. Bxb5 axb5 34. Nb6 Rcxb6 35. axb6 Rxb6 36. Rd5 c4 37. Qb4 Nd8 38. Rb1 Nb7 39. Rxb5 Rxb5 40. Qxb5 Qxb5 41. Rxb5 Nxd6 42. Rb6 Nf5 43. Kf2 Ne7 44. Rb7 Kf7 45. Rc7 h5 46. Rxc4 Ke6 47. Ra4 g5 48. Ra6+ Kf7 49. g4 h4 50. Ke2 Nd5 51. Rd6 1-0[Event "Western States op"]
