1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. c4 Bg7 4. Nc3 O-O 5. Bg5 d6 6. e3 c6 7. Be2 a6 { Against the ...a6-c6-b5 plan, the best thing to do is to ignore it and continue with our development! } 8. O-O ( { If White prevents ...b5 with } 8. a4 $6 { Black will happily play } 8... a5 9. O-O Na6 $13 ) 8... b5 9. Nd2 $14 ( { The "lazy" } 9. a3 $14 { is possible. After preventing ...b4, White continues with his development. } 9... bxc4 10. Bxc4 $14 ) ( 9. Rc1 $14 ) 9... bxc4 10. Nxc4 { White is better - with nice development and weaknesses to play against. } 10... a5 11. Rc1 Ba6 12. Re1 $5 { Overprotecting the bishop. } 12... Nbd7 13. Na4 { After all the pieces have been developed White starts some active play. } 13... Bb5 14. Na3 Bxa4 15. Qxa4 c5 16. Nb5 Qb6 17. Rc2 Rfc8 18. Rec1 Rab8 19. h3 Rc6 20. Na3 $16 { [%cal Ya3c4] } 20... Rc7 21. Bb5 Kf8 22. b3 Qb7 23. Bxf6 Bxf6 24. Bxd7 Rxd7 25. dxc5 dxc5 26. Nc4 Rbd8 27. Re2 Rd5 28. Qxa5 Rd1+ 29. Rxd1 Rxd1+ 30. Re1 Qd5 31. Rxd1 Qxd1+ 32. Kh2 1-0[Event "World op 37th"]
