1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Bg5 d6 5. e3 h6 6. Bh4 O-O 7. Be2 $5 ( { Also playable is } 7. Bd3 { , when White can handle the position in a different way: } 7... c5 8. d5 e6 9. dxe6 Bxe6 10. Nge2 Nc6 11. Nf4 g5 12. Nxe6 fxe6 13. Bg3 ) 7... Nbd7 8. Nf3 c6 9. O-O g5 ( 9... Qa5 $2 { does not make sense as it runs into a later Rb1-b4. } ) 10. Bg3 Nh5 11. Nd2 Nxg3 12. hxg3 { A good position for White but also playable with Black. Black has the two bishops but also some weaknesses. } 12... f5 ( 12... e5 $6 13. d5 $5 { Now g4 is a positional threat. } ( 13. dxe5 dxe5 ( 13... Nxe5 14. Nde4 $16 { [%csl Rd6] } ) 14. g4 $16 { Securing e4 for the knight. } 14... Nc5 15. Nde4 Nxe4 16. Nxe4 Qxd1 17. Rfxd1 ) 13... f5 ( 13... a6 $2 14. g4 $16 { [%cal Yd2e4] White has established control of the light squares in the center. } ) 14. g4 $1 f4 $14 15. Nde4 $16 ) 13. Qc2 { With chances for both sides. } 13... e6 14. Rad1 Nf6 $6 15. Bd3 ( 15. e4 $14 ) 15... d5 16. b4 Ne4 17. b5 Nxc3 18. Qxc3 c5 19. Nb3 cxd4 20. exd4 f4 21. cxd5 exd5 22. gxf4 gxf4 23. f3 Bf5 24. Bxf5 Rxf5 25. Rfe1 Rc8 26. Qd3 Rh5 27. Re5 Bxe5 28. Qg6+ Bg7 29. Qxh5 Qg5 30. Qh3 Rc2 31. Re1 Kh7 32. Kh2 Rxa2 33. Nc5 Qg3+ 34. Qxg3 fxg3+ 35. Kxg3 Bxd4 36. Rc1 Bxc5 37. Rxc5 d4 38. Rc7+ Kg6 39. Rxb7 d3 40. Rd7 d2 41. Kf4 Kf6 42. g4 Ke6 43. Rd8 Ke7 44. Rd3 Kf6 45. Ke3 Rb2 46. Rxd2 Rxb5 47. Rd6+ Kg5 48. Ra6 Rb3+ 49. Kf2 1-0[Event "?"]
