1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Bg5 h6 5. Bh4 d6 6. e3 O-O 7. Nf3 a5 $2 {Even top players can play bad random moves (especially in blitz) !} 8. Be2 b6 9. O-O Bb7 {White has more than one good move:} 10. Nd2 $14 (10. Qc2 $14 g5 $2 {This is a mistake. If Black plays ...g5 he must be ready to follow up with ... Nh5 - which isn't possible after 10.Qc2:} 11. Bg3 Nh5 $2 (11... e6 12. h3 $14 {/}) 12. Nxg5 $1 hxg5 13. Bxh5 {Black has no compensation, e.g.} f5 14. f4 ({or} 14. Be2 f4 15. exf4 gxf4 16. Bh4 $18) 14... gxf4 (14... g4 15. Bh4 $18) 15. Rxf4 $18 (15. Bh4 $18)) (10. d5 $14 {with the idea of Nd4 is also playable. For instance} e5 (10... c5 11. Nd2 Nbd7 12. e4 $16 {[%csl Ra5,Rb5,Rb7,Gc4,Gd5,Ge4,Gf4][%cal Yf2f4]}) 11. Nd2 $16 (11. dxe6 $5 fxe6 12. Nd4 $14 Qe8 13. f4 e5 14. Ndb5 $14)) 10... Nbd7 11. Bf3 (11. f4 $16 {[%cal Yf4f5]}) (11. Qc2 $5) 11... Qc8 12. h3 Re8 13. Bxb7 Qxb7 14. Qf3 $2 (14. f4 $14 {/}) 14... c6 $2 (14... Qxf3 $11) 15. Rfd1 $14 a4 16. Rac1 Reb8 17. Qe2 b5 18. cxb5 cxb5 19. Qf3 Qxf3 20. Nxf3 b4 21. Nb1 g5 22. Bg3 Ne4 23. Bh2 f5 24. Nfd2 Nef6 25. Nc4 Nd5 26. f3 N7b6 27. Nxb6 Rxb6 28. Kf2 f4 29. exf4 gxf4 30. Ke2 Kf7 31. Kd3 Rb5 32. Re1 Kg6 33. Re4 Kf5 34. Nd2 Bf6 35. Nf1 Bh4 36. Re2 Rg8 37. Rc6 a3 38. b3 Rbb8 39. Ra6 Ra8 40. Rxa8 Rxa8 41. Rc2 Rg8 42. Re2 h5 43. Rc2 Nc3 44. Rd2 Rc8 45. Rc2 e5 46. Nd2 $19 exd4 47. Nc4 Rc6 48. Kxd4 d5 49. Na5 Nb5+ 50. Kd3 Rxc2 51. Kxc2 Nc3 52. Nc6 Nxa2 53. Bg1 Be1 54. Bc5 Ke6 55. Nd4+ Kd7 56. Ne2 Nc3 57. Bxb4 Nxe2 58. Bxe1 Nd4+ 59. Kb1 Nxb3 60. Ka2 Nc1+ 61. Kxa3 d4 62. Bd2 Ne2 63. Kb4 Ke6 64. Kc4 Ke5 65. Kd3 Ng3 66. Be1 Nf5 67. Bf2 Ne3 68. g3 fxg3 69. Bxg3+ Kd5 70. Bf2 Nf5 71. f4 Kc5 72. Ke4 Nd6+ 73. Ke5 Nc4+ 74. Ke4 Nd2+ 75. Kd3 Nb3 76. Ke4 Kc4 77. f5 d3 78. Be3 Nc5+ 79. Ke5 Nd7+ 80. Ke6 Nb6 81. f6 Nd5 82. Bd2 Nxf6 83. Kxf6 Kd4 84. Kg5 Ke4 85. Kxh5 Kf3 86. h4 Ke4 87. Kg6 Kf3 88. h5 Ke4 89. h6 Kf3 90. h7 Ke4 91. h8=Q Kf3 92. Qe5 Kf2 93. Qe3+ Kf1 94. Qxd3+ Kf2 95. Qe3+ Kf1 96. Qf3+ Kg1 97. Be3+ Kh2 98. Qg4 1-0

