1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Bg5 O-O 5. e3 d6 6. Be2 Nbd7 7. Nf3 h6 8. Bh4 c6 9. O-O Qe8 10. Qc2 e5 11. dxe5 (11. Rfd1 $5) (11. h3 $5) 11... dxe5 (11... Nxe5 12. Nd4 Bd7 13. Rad1 $16 {[%csl Rd6]} ({Maybe even} 13. e4 {with the idea of f4 is good.})) 12. Nd2 $14 Qe6 $2 {Now we can play either b4-c5 with the idea of transferring a piece to c4 or b4-b5 - depending on Black's reaction!} 13. b4 $16 a5 14. a3 c5 15. b5 {White will continue with Bf3 and play on the light squares.} (15. bxa5 {also makes sense - White can use the weakened b5- and d5-squares.} Rxa5 16. e4 ({or} 16. Nb5) 16... Ra8 ({Transferring the knight to d4 does not work now:} 16... Nb8 $2 17. Nb3 {[%csl Ra5,Rc5][%cal Yb3c5,Yb3a5]}) 17. Nd5 $16) 15... b6 16. Bf3 Rb8 17. Rad1 g5 18. Bg3 g4 19. Bc6 Bb7 20. Nd5 Nxd5 (20... Bxc6 21. bxc6 Qxc6 $4 22. Ne7+ $18) 21. cxd5 Qe7 22. e4 {White wants to play Nc4 but first he stops Black's counterplay.} (22. Nc4 f5) 22... Bc8 23. Nc4 $18 {Black is completely lost.} h5 24. d6 Qg5 25. Qd2 (25. f4 $5) 25... Qg6 26. Rfe1 Rd8 27. Bxd7 Bxd7 28. a4 Re8 29. Qd3 Re6 30. Ne3 Ree8 31. Nf5 Bf8 32. Bh4 f6 33. Qd5+ Kh7 34. Ne7 Qh6 35. Nc6 Rbc8 36. Rd3 Bg7 37. Qf7 Be6 38. Qb7 Rb8 39. Nxb8 Bc4 40. Rdd1 f5 41. d7 Rf8 42. d8=Q Rxd8 43. Bxd8 fxe4 44. Rd7 e3 45. Rxg7+ Qxg7 46. Qxg7+ Kxg7 47. Rxe3 Bb3 48. Bxb6 Bxa4 49. Bxc5 Bxb5 50. Rxe5 a4 51. Bd4 1-0

