1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Bg5 d6 5. e3 h6 6. Bh4 c6 7. Nf3 Bf5 8. Be2 (8. Bd3 $1 {this is even more simple !} Bxd3 9. Qxd3 Nbd7 10. O-O O-O 11. h3 $14 (11. Rfd1 $14) (11. Rad1 $14)) 8... O-O (8... Ne4 $5 9. Nxe4 Bxe4 10. O-O $14) 9. Nd2 d5 $2 {This move does not fit at all with Black's plans!} 10. Qb3 $16 (10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. cxd5 cxd5 12. Qb3) 10... g5 11. Qxb7 {A risky move. In better positions, we should not go for complications unless we have calculated everything!} ({Much simpler is} 11. Bg3 $1 {, for instance} Qb6 12. cxd5 Qxb3 (12... cxd5 13. O-O $16) 13. Nxb3 Nxd5 (13... cxd5 14. Rc1 Nc6 15. Nc5 $18) 14. Na5 $16) 11... gxh4 12. Qxa8 Qb6 {White's queen is in danger and he must play very accurately.} 13. Na4 $1 Qa5 $2 ({After} 13... Qc7 {White is better but must remain careful:} 14. Nc5 Bc8 15. Rc1 $14) 14. Nc5 $18 h3 15. gxh3 Ne4 16. Ncxe4 Bxe4 17. f3 Bf5 18. Qb7 Na6 19. Qb3 c5 20. Qc3 Qb6 21. Rg1 cxd4 22. Qxd4 Qxd4 23. exd4 Nb4 24. Kf2 Kh7 25. Nb3 a5 26. Rxg7+ Kxg7 27. Nxa5 Ra8 28. Nb3 dxc4 29. Bxc4 Rxa2 30. Rxa2 Nxa2 31. Nc5 Nb4 32. Ne4 Nc2 33. d5 Nb4 34. h4 h5 35. Ke3 Bd7 36. Kd4 Ba4 37. b3 Nc2+ 38. Kc3 Ne1 39. bxa4 Nxf3 40. a5 Ne5 41. Bb5 f5 42. Nc5 f4 43. a6 f3 44. Ne4 Ng4 45. a7 f2 46. a8=Q Nxh2 47. Nxf2 Nf3 48. Qd8 Kf7 49. d6 exd6 50. Qd7+ Kf6 51. Qxd6+ Kf5 52. Bd7# 1-0

