1. d4 d6 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. c4 g6 4. Nc3 Bf5 ( { The position in the game is also reached after } 4... Bg7 5. Bg5 O-O 6. e3 Bf5 7. Bd3 $14 ) 5. Bg5 ( 5. Qb3 $14 ) 5... Bg7 6. e3 O-O 7. Bd3 $14 { The simplest approach! } 7... Bxd3 8. Qxd3 Nbd7 9. h3 { White is preparing to transfer her bishop to the h2-b8 diagonal. } 9... h6 10. Bf4 Qe8 11. Bh2 e5 12. Qe2 ( { Here the idea of } 12. dxe5 dxe5 13. Nd2 $6 { is not effective. Firstly, d6 is not weak and secondly, White loses some time: } 13... Nc5 14. Qc2 Rd8 $13 ) ( 12. Qc2 $14 ) 12... c6 13. O-O Qe7 14. Rfd1 Rfe8 $16 15. Rac1 a6 16. Qc2 { Now White is ready to expand on the Queenside. } 16... e4 { This is usually a bad move. } 17. Nd2 $16 Nf8 18. Re1 { Not necessary though White still remains better. } ( 18. b4 $16 ) 18... Rad8 19. b4 g5 20. b5 { White has the faster attack and managed to win. } 20... Ng6 21. bxc6 bxc6 22. Rb1 d5 23. Ne2 g4 24. cxd5 gxh3 25. dxc6 Qe6 26. c7 Rc8 27. Rb8 hxg2 28. Rxc8 Rxc8 29. Kxg2 h5 30. Nf4 Qg4+ 31. Kh1 Nxf4 32. exf4 Qh3 33. Re3 Qh4 34. Nf1 Ng4 35. Re2 Bxd4 36. Kg2 Nxf2 37. Rxf2 Qg4+ 38. Bg3 Bxf2 39. Kxf2 h4 40. Bh2 Qd7 41. f5 Qxf5+ 42. Ke1 Qf3 43. Qc5 Kh7 44. Qe3 Qf5 45. Qf2 Qa5+ 46. Nd2 f5 47. Qxh4+ Kg6 48. Bf4 e3 49. Qg3+ Kf7 50. Qxe3 Qxa2 51. Qe5 Kg8 52. Qf6 Qd5 53. Be5 Rxc7 54. Bxc7 Qf7 55. Qd8+ Kh7 56. Be5 Kg6 57. Nf3 f4 58. Qg5+ Kh7 59. Qh4+ 1-0[Event "GREAT GAME!"]
