{ White achieved a very clear win - this is how we must play! } 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. Bg5 Bg7 4. e3 O-O 5. Be2 d6 6. c4 Nbd7 7. Nc3 c6 8. Qc2 Qc7 ( { The idea with ...h6, ...g5, and ...Nh5 does not work after 8.Qc2: } 8... h6 9. Bh4 g5 10. Bg3 Nh5 $2 11. Nxg5 $16 Nxg3 $4 12. Qh7# ( 12. hxg3 hxg5 13. Qh7# ) ) 9. O-O h6 10. Bh4 Re8 11. Rfd1 ( { Preparing the transfer of the bishop to g3 makes a lot of sense as Black's queen turns out to be misplaced on c7. } 11. h3 $5 e5 12. Bg3 $16 ) 11... b6 12. h3 $1 Bb7 13. b4 Rac8 14. a4 $16 { By simple means White is much better! } 14... a5 15. bxa5 $1 { Opening up the Queenside. } 15... bxa5 16. Bg3 $16 { Threatening c4-c5! } 16... c5 17. d5 Rb8 18. Nb5 Qd8 19. Rab1 $18 { White has a strategically winning position. } 19... g5 20. Nd2 Nf8 21. f4 gxf4 22. exf4 Qd7 23. f5 $1 N8h7 24. Nb3 Ra8 25. Bd3 Kh8 26. Be1 $5 { White decides to win on the Queenside. He could have also started an attack on the Kingside, with for instance Bf4. } 26... Nh5 27. Nxa5 Rxa5 28. Bxa5 Rg8 29. Re1 Nf4 30. Bd2 Nxh3+ 31. gxh3 Be5+ 32. Kf1 Ng5 33. Re3 e6 34. Bc3 exd5 35. cxd5 Bxd5 36. Nxd6 f6 37. Bxe5 fxe5 38. Qxc5 Bf3 39. Qxe5+ 1-0[Event "Rated game, 3 min"]
