{ An amazing game by White! } 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Nf3 O-O 5. Bg5 c5 6. d5 d6 7. e3 h6 8. Bh4 g5 9. Bg3 Nh5 10. Bd3 Nxg3 { Black needs to take the bishop. } ( 10... a6 $2 { allows } 11. Nxg5 $1 Nxg3 12. hxg3 hxg5 13. Bh7+ ( 13. Qh5 $6 Re8 ) 13... Kh8 14. Qh5 Re8 15. Bg6+ Kg8 16. Bxf7+ Kf8 17. Be6 $18 ) 11. hxg3 e6 12. Bc2 $16 ( 12. Qc2 $16 exd5 13. Nxd5 $1 ) 12... e5 { Now White played a good strategic move: } ( 12... f5 13. g4 $16 ( 13. e4 $1 ) ) ( 12... exd5 13. Nxd5 $5 { Here we can go for active piece play. } 13... Qa5+ 14. Kf1 $16 { White's king is safe on f1. White's h1-rook is already on an open file and we have strong threats on the Kingside. } ) 13. e4 $16 { This needs to be played - White is fighting against ...f5 and closes the diagonal of the g7-bishop. With the pawn on g6 instead of g5, Black would be better but here White has a strategically winning position. } 13... Nd7 14. Nd2 a6 15. a4 Qb6 16. Qc1 f5 { Black cannot wait passively as White just improves his position. } ( 16... Nf6 17. Nf1 Bd7 18. Ne3 $16 ) 17. exf5 Nf6 18. a5 Qd8 19. Qb1 ( { Castling short was very good: } 19. O-O Bd7 20. Nde4 Nxe4 21. Bxe4 Bxf5 22. Bxf5 Rxf5 23. Ne4 $18 { White will prepare b4 with a winning position. } ) 19... b5 20. axb6 Qxb6 21. Nce4 Nxe4 22. Bxe4 Rb8 23. b3 g4 24. O-O h5 25. Qd3 Bh6 26. f3 Rb7 27. fxg4 hxg4 28. f6 Qb4 29. Rad1 Rbf7 30. Bf5 Bxd2 31. Bxc8 1-0[Event "?"]
