{ A nice game by White against a line with ...Bf5. } 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Nf3 d6 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 g5 7. Bg3 Bf5 8. e3 c5 9. Bd3 $16 ( 9. d5 $4 { We know the plans, BUT WE MUST KEEP OUR EYES OPEN! In this concrete position d5 is a mistake! } 9... Qb6 $17 ( 9... Ne4 $15 ) ) 9... Bxd3 10. Qxd3 $16 Nc6 ( 10... cxd4 $2 11. Nxd4 $16 ) 11. d5 { Now this is fine. } 11... Nb4 12. Qe2 Nh5 13. O-O Nxg3 14. fxg3 $16 { You won't see this idea often but here it is very good! Black has weakened his position with ...h6-g5 and has a terrible knight on b4. } ( 14. hxg3 { also makes sense, for instance } 14... O-O 15. Nd2 Na6 16. g4 Nc7 17. g3 $16 { [%cal Yg1g2,Yf2f4] } ) 14... Qd7 15. a3 Na6 16. Qd3 O-O 17. Rf2 Nc7 18. Raf1 e6 19. h4 g4 20. Nh2 exd5 21. Rf5 dxc4 22. Qxc4 Qe6 23. Qf4 h5 24. Rxh5 f5 25. Rxf5 Rxf5 26. Qxf5 Qxe3+ 27. Kh1 Rf8 28. Qxg4 Ne6 29. Nf3 Nd4 30. Re1 Qf2 31. Ne4 Qxb2 32. Nfg5 d5 33. Qh5 Rf5 34. Nd6 1-0[Event "Sigeman & Co 14th"]
