1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Bg5 O-O 5. e3 c5 6. d5 h6 7. Bh4 Qb6 $6 8. Rb1 d6 9. Bd3 $1 ( { or } 9. Nf3 $1 { , for instance } 9... g5 ( 9... Bf5 10. Bd3 $16 ) 10. Bg3 Nh5 11. Bd3 Nxg3 12. hxg3 Qa5 $2 13. Qc2 $16 { is simple and good. } ( 13. Nxg5 $3 { leads to a decisive attack though this is difficult to calculate for a human. } 13... f5 ( 13... hxg5 14. Bh7+ Kh8 15. Qh5 $18 ) 14. Rxh6 $3 Bxh6 15. Qh5 Kg7 16. g4 $18 { and despite being down a rook White's attack is decisive. White can continue with Ke2!, allowing the rook to join the attack. } ) ) 9... e5 10. dxe6 $14 { Makes sense in this position. White wants to play against Black's weaknesses on the d-file. } ( 10. h3 $16 ) 10... Bxe6 11. Nge2 Nc6 12. O-O Ne5 13. b3 g5 14. Bg3 Rad8 15. Bc2 Nh5 16. f4 Ng4 17. Qd3 f5 18. fxg5 hxg5 19. Nd5 Ne5 20. Bxe5 dxe5 21. Nxb6 Rxd3 22. Bxd3 axb6 23. g4 e4 24. Bc2 Nf6 25. gxf5 Bd7 26. Rbd1 Bc6 27. h3 b5 28. Rd2 Ra8 29. Bb1 bxc4 30. bxc4 Ra3 31. Kf2 Kf7 32. Nc1 g4 33. Nb3 gxh3 34. Kg3 Ra8 35. Kxh3 Rh8+ 36. Kg3 Nd7 37. f6 Bxf6 38. Bxe4 Bxe4 39. Rxd7+ Ke8 40. Rxf6 1-0[Event "EU-ch rapid"]
