1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. d4 O-O 5. Bg5 c5 6. d5 d6 7. e3 e6 $2 ( { The same motif exists after } 7... h6 8. Bh4 e6 $2 9. Nd2 $1 ) 8. Nd2 $16 { Black will play this after any other move than ...g5 - with a great version of the Benoni for White! } 8... exd5 9. cxd5 a6 10. a4 Re8 11. Be2 Nbd7 12. O-O Rb8 13. Qc2 ( 13. h3 { also fits perfectly with White's ideas. White may continue with e4,f4. For instance } 13... h6 14. Bh4 Ne5 15. f4 Ned7 16. e4 b6 17. Nc4 $18 ( { The typical pawn sacrifice also needs to be checked! } 17. e5 dxe5 18. f5 ) ) 13... Ne5 14. h3 $1 { Now White should play this move, covering g4, to have ideas with f4! } 14... h6 15. Bh4 Qc7 16. b3 $16 ( 16. e4 $16 ) ( 16. Bg3 $16 ) 16... Bf5 17. e4 Bc8 18. f4 { Black's position is disastrous. } 18... Ned7 19. Kh1 { A useful prophylactic move. } 19... Nh7 20. Rad1 { Quietly strengthening his position - Black has no plan. } 20... g5 21. Bg3 gxf4 22. Bxf4 Ne5 { Black now has a nice square on e5 but has seriously weakened his king. } 23. Rf2 { Intending to double the rooks. } ( 23. Nc4 Nxc4 24. Bxc4 $16 { /+- } ) 23... Ng6 24. Bh2 Be5 25. Rdf1 Re7 26. Bh5 b5 27. Bxg6 fxg6 28. Bxe5 Rxe5 29. Nf3 Re8 30. axb5 axb5 31. e5 Bf5 32. Qd2 b4 33. Ne2 dxe5 34. Nh4 c4 35. d6 Qg7 36. bxc4 b3 37. Nxf5 gxf5 38. Rxf5 b2 39. Nc3 e4 40. Rb5 Rxb5 41. cxb5 e3 42. Qxb2 Ng5 43. Qb3+ Kh8 44. Ne2 Qd7 45. Qc3+ Kg8 46. Qc6 Rd8 47. Rd1 Qf5 48. d7 Ne4 49. Qd5+ Qxd5 50. Rxd5 Nf6 51. Rd6 Kf7 52. Rd3 Rxd7 53. Rxe3 Rd1+ 54. Kh2 Rb1 55. Nc3 Rb3 56. Kg3 Rxc3 57. Rxc3 Ne4+ 58. Kh4 Nxc3 59. b6 Ne4 1-0[Event "?"]
