1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Bg5 O-O 5. e3 d6 6. Nf3 c5 7. d5 a6 8. Nd2 $16 h6 9. Bh4 b5 { The Benko Gambit does not really work against the Smyslov KID. Black cannot even force us to play Kxf1 like in the normal Benko accepted! However, if Black does not play ...b5, we would prevent it forever with a4! } ( 9... Re8 10. a4 $16 ) ( 9... e6 10. a4 $16 ) ( 9... Nbd7 10. a4 $16 ) 10. cxb5 axb5 11. Bxb5 Ba6 12. a4 $18 { a4! is always the best idea here, if it is not blundering anything! } 12... Qa5 13. Ra3 Qb4 14. Bxf6 $1 { White can even give up his dark-squared bishop as he manages to stabilize the position! } 14... Bxf6 15. Rb3 Qh4 16. h3 Qg5 17. Nf3 Qf5 ( 17... Qxg2 $2 18. Rh2 $18 ) 18. O-O g5 19. e4 Qg6 20. Re1 Bxb5 21. Rxb5 Nd7 22. Rb7 Rfd8 23. Re3 Kh8 24. b3 Rab8 25. Rxb8 Rxb8 26. Nb1 g4 27. hxg4 Qxg4 28. Qf1 Rg8 29. Nbd2 Ne5 30. g3 Nxf3+ 31. Nxf3 Bd4 32. Nxd4 cxd4 33. Qa1 Qg7 34. Rd3 Rb8 35. a5 Qe5 36. Qxd4 Qxd4 37. Rxd4 Rxb3 38. Ra4 Rb7 39. a6 Ra7 40. f4 Kg7 41. Kg2 Kf6 42. Kh3 Kg6 43. Kg4 h5+ 44. Kh4 e6 45. dxe6 fxe6 46. Ra5 1-0[Event "Pardubice KB op"]
