1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 d6 3. Nc3 Nbd7 ( { or } 3... e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 ( 4... e4 5. Ng5 $16 ) ( 4... exd4 5. Nxd4 Be7 6. e4 { White can also play Bg5 followed by e3, but we need not be obsessed with it. 6.e4 is simple and strong. } 6... O-O 7. Be2 $16 { White has everything he could wish for. } ) 5. Bg5 ) 4. Nf3 e5 5. Bg5 Be7 ( 5... g6 6. e3 { transposes to the King's Indian. } ) 6. e3 O-O 7. Be2 ( { The immediate } 7. Qc2 c6 8. O-O-O $5 { is also possible - see model game Mastrovasilis-Kanarakis. } ) 7... c6 8. Qc2 Re8 { Now White can decide wether to castle short or long - it is a matter of taste. } 9. O-O { I prefer this. For example } ( 9. O-O-O { possibly followed by h4, g4 with attacking chances is also playable. } ) 9... h6 10. Bh4 Qc7 ( 10... exd4 11. Nxd4 { Whenever Black takes on d4 we usually take with the knight (though exd4 is playable) . } ) 11. h3 $5 { As in the Smyslov System, transferring the bishop to g3 is a good idea! } 11... Nf8 12. Bg3 $16 *[Event "?"]
