1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 d6 3. Nc3 Nbd7 4. Nf3 e5 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 O-O 7. Qc2 { With this White immediately prepares 0-0-0. } 7... c6 8. O-O-O $5 Qa5 ( 8... a6 $2 { is not possible as White is threatening to take on e5. } 9. dxe5 dxe5 10. Nxe5 $18 ) 9. Bd3 { Threatening to take on h7 as the f6-knight is pinned. } 9... Re8 10. h4 h6 11. Bf5 { White wants to keep his bishop on g5 as taking it leads to a strong attack on the h-file. This strategy is however double-edged and could also backfire. } 11... e4 12. Bxe4 Nxe4 13. Qxe4 hxg5 $2 { Now White gets a decisive attack. Strong was 13...d5 instead. } 14. hxg5 Nf8 15. Qh4 $18 f6 16. Qh8+ Kf7 17. Rh7 $1 { White plays the attack in an inspired fashion. } 17... Bf5 ( 17... Nxh7 18. g6+ $18 ) 18. Rxg7+ Ke6 19. d5+ Kd7 20. gxf6 1-0[Event "Pan-Am Intercollegiate"]
