{ In this game, White achieved a clear advantage with simple moves. Later though, Black managed to win! } 1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 e5 3. Nf3 d6 4. d4 Nbd7 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 O-O 7. Qc2 h6 8. Bh4 exd4 9. Nxd4 Nd5 { Unusual and playable but not enough to equalize. } ( 9... Ne5 10. Be2 Ng6 11. Bg3 { White is going to castle short and has a very pleasant advantage. } ) 10. Bxe7 Nxe7 11. Be2 Nc6 12. Rd1 $16 { Even if the outcome of the game was negative, the outcome of the opening is a success for White. } 12... Nxd4 13. Rxd4 Ne5 14. O-O b6 15. f4 $1 Nc6 16. Rdd1 f5 17. e4 $1 Bd7 18. Bf3 fxe4 19. Qxe4 Rc8 20. Nd5 Bf5 21. Qe3 Qd7 22. Rfe1 Rce8 23. Qc3 Nd8 24. Bh5 Rxe1+ 25. Rxe1 Be6 26. Qg3 Bxd5 27. cxd5 Qb5 28. Re7 Qc5+ 29. Qe3 Qxd5 30. Bf3 Qxa2 31. Qc3 Ne6 32. g3 c5 33. b3 Nd4 34. Bd5+ Kh8 35. Qd3 Nf5 36. Rd7 Re8 37. Be6 g6 38. Qe4 Qd2 39. Qb7 Qe1+ 40. Kg2 Qxe6 0-1[Event "?"]
